## General

## Library
* When Favourites sync takes longer then 5 seconds for a gallery, display the gallery name

* Fix some sources not updating when grouping by source
* Fix library bottom bar display getting stuck

## Sources
### ExHentai/E-Hentai
* Search EHentai uploader on click
* Fix EH/ExhHentai duplicate results in search

### Merged
* Add way to open merged mangas in webview
* Fix merged manga delete after read

* Improve Hitomi tag list

* Better support tag search

* MangaDex Random
* And a few others that I cant think of at the top of my head

* Improve filter by scanlator to handle all sources
* Rename manga directory if title changes

* Fix crash when opening reader or webview during migration

* Fix and improve Batch add (By @D3xron)

## Library
* Dynamic Categories, inspired by J2ks feature, but written from the ground up, quickly organize your library into different sets of categories, by source, status, and tracking, or totally ungrouped, its in the library bottom sheet
* Continue reading button, inspired by J2ks feature, it will take you to the first unread chapter, can be toggled in the library bottom sheet
* Redo drag and drop, now you can drag and drop in any mode, and it will switch your mode to it when you drag and drop something
* Quick clean Titles, adds a quick clean that will clean titles from manga from certain sources, it will quickly remove unnecessary bloat
* Rewrite the library search engine (that was inherited from EH), it now can exclude, use quotes for absolute searches, it supports namespace tags, and a bunch more, its probably the most advanced search engine any Tachi fork has
* Fix pressing download unread chapters on an Exh manga would download the latest chapter even if it was read

Features of Tachiyomi(original) include:
* Online reading from sources such as MangaDex, MangaSee, Mangakakalot, [and more](https://github.com/inorichi/tachiyomi-extensions)
* Local reading of downloaded manga
* A configurable reader with multiple viewers, reading directions and other settings.
* [MyAnimeList](https://myanimelist.net/), [AniList](https://anilist.co/), [Kitsu](https://kitsu.io/), [Shikimori](https://shikimori.one), and [Bangumi](https://bgm.tv/) support
* Categories to organize your library
* Light and dark themes
* Schedule updating your library for new chapters
* Create backups locally to read offline or to your desired cloud service

Features of TachiyomiSY include:
* Uses the new Tachiyomi Stable UI
* Custom manga page, all your needs, such as info and chapters, in front of your face
* Latest tab, store up to 5 sources where you can easily view the latest manga by viewing the tab
* Hentai features enable/disable, in advanced settings
* Automatic webtoon detection, allowing the reader to switch to webtoon mode automatically when viewing one

rockit.description: Rock It! is an Android app that helps you stay informed on all things space

nodes.description:
- Added a search page. You can now search launches and events easily.
- The launch details page now shows more info on boosters and landings
- Improve date display for things within the next week

- Added a new page that shows launches and events you're subscribed to
- The planet spinner loading animation now looks a bit nicer 
- Only run background tasks if the network is available

Changes:
- Make notifications actually open the respective page in the app
- Display day names and times for days within the next week (instead of only the date)
- Fix weird bouncing scroll when leaving the last detail view of a list
- Load 50 launches / events at once (instead of 25), this makes it less likely to get limited by the server


Please note that launches you were subscribed to before this update might get wrong notifications (the ones that were already scheduled) at some point due to the notification logic being changed.
Remove German translation as mixing German UI with English data is kind of ugly

Changes:
* Improve date format for negative countdown values
* Article Cards: Improve news site overlay
* Make article cards larger
* Improve logic for launch/event update notifications
* Improve date format for current year in launches/events listing

Changes:
* Add a custom loading animation
* Always show domain in article widgets

- Switching countdown modes now no longer requires tapping the text exactly, only the widget *with* the text
- Make launch details page look a bit better
- Allow images to be larger on event & launch details pages, looks better
- Improve web experience: update icons, metadata & data fetching

Changes:
* Redesign credits page
* Add app download button to web version

Changes:
* Copy links when holding long on all linking widgets
* Improve loading of launches, events and articles
* Add landscape mode for event/launch listing
* Build the app for web, now available on [my website](https://rockit.010.one/#/)

This is finally the release of version 1.0 of the app. It now has all initially planned *basic* features and has undergone many design overhauls.

**Features**

- List upcoming launches and events (e.g. space station activity)
- Show launch/event details and a countdown (including the date and time in your local timezone)
- List latest space news articles
- Subscribe to launches or events to receive notifications before the start or when times are updated
- Localization for English and German (UI only, data is in English)
- No internet? No problem! The app caches offline content for a few days and updates it when connected to the internet

Installation can be done as described in the README of the project.

- **Subscribe to events to receive notifications**
- **Render program info (e.g. the Starship program) in launch & event details**
- Generally a lot of improvements for date formats (also respect 24h date format setting)
- Dates are now shown in a more friendly manner (e.g. "Today, 12:30" etc)
- Improved error handling (you can now retry everything that could fail)
- Improved notification scheduling

* Add ripple effect to article cards 
* Custom, colored app bar that looks better
* Efficiency improvements in page layout rebuilding
* More bouncing effects
* Launch/Event images now fill up the entire area they are allowed to

* Render updates for events
* Improve date formats by including the week day where it makes sense

See #2
You can now subscribe to a launch to receive notifications before liftoff.

* **New**: event listing & details view
* Vast improvements to basically everything, more animations etc.

* Swipe through launches after opening one
* Show launch info updates (e.g. liftoff, updates on the status etc.)
The app now uses previously downloaded responses in case something doesn't work while downloading the latest updates.
In case the API rate-limits you, you can still see the previous response
The design is now a bit better

This initial release contains the very basic app. 
It displays upcoming launches and space news.
